Mat 21:5 <mark class='poetry'></mark> <strong><mark class='verb'>Εἴπατε</mark></strong> <strong>τῇ</strong> <strong>θυγατρὶ</strong> <strong>Σιών <mark class='punctuation'>·</mark> </strong> <mark class='poetry'></mark> Ἰδοὺ <strong>ὁ</strong> <strong>Βασιλεύς</strong> <strong>σου</strong> <strong><mark class='verb'>ἔρχεταί</mark></strong> <strong>σοι</strong> <mark class='poetry'></mark> <strong>πραῢς</strong> <strong>καὶ</strong> <strong><mark class='ptc'>ἐπιβεβηκὼς</mark></strong> <strong>ἐπὶ</strong> <strong>ὄνον</strong> <mark class='poetry'></mark> <strong>καὶ</strong> <strong>ἐπὶ</strong> <strong>πῶλον</strong> <strong>υἱὸν</strong> <strong>ὑποζυγίου <mark class='punctuation'>.</mark>  </strong>【要對錫安的居民（原文是女子）說：看哪，你的王來到你這裡，是溫柔的，又騎著驢，就是騎著驢駒子。】<mark class='paragraph'></mark>
